    <stitle>GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - TROUBLESHOOTING - VOLTMETER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>VOLTMETER</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Voltmeter Circuits From Speedo/Tach Module To Gauge Cluster (Mechanical And Electronic
                Engine)
            </title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08035x_17.xml" xrefid="x0803512">VOLTMETER</hotlnk>
                for operation description of the voltmeter.
            </para>
            <table id="t0803524" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Voltmeter Circuits From Speedo/Tach Module To Gauge Cluster (Mechanical And Electronic
                    Engine)
                </title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.55in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.84in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.31in"/>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Remove connector (422) from Speedo/Tach module and remove connector (424) from the
                                    gauge cluster. At connector (424) measure resistance to ground at circuits 27S(+),
                                    27S(-), 27C(+) and 27C(-).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(424) circuits 27S, and 27C to gnd</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with less than 100K ohms, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>At connector (424) measure resistance between circuits 27S(+), 27S(-), 27C(+) and
                                    27C(-) and between all other circuits in the connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(424) circuits 27S and 27C and all other circuits</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate short between any circuits with less than 100K ohms resistance between
                                    terminals, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Measure resistance of circuits 27S(+), 27S(-), 27C(+) and 27C(-) between
                                    connectors (422) and (424).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(424) and (422)</para>
                                <para>circuits 27S and 27C</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Locate open in any circuit having more than 5 ohms resistance, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Remove voltmeter. At gauge cluster side of connector (424) measure resistance
                                    between terminals 9, 10, 11, 12.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(424)</para>
                                <para>terminals 9, 10, 11, 12</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>> or = 100K Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (424) terminals 9, 10, 11, 12 and the
                                    corresponding gauge terminal connections in the cluster.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>(424)</para>
                                <para>terminals 9, 10, 11, 12</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>&#60; or = 5 Ohms?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Replace the cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>The circuits between the Speedo/Tach module and voltmeter cluster terminals check
                                    good. If this test was performed , replace the Speedo/Tach module. If not, perform
                                    steps in
                                    <hotlnk document="s08035x_40.xml" xrefid="x0803508">GAUGE CIRCUIT
                                        TROUBLESHOOTING</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
